✅ What is Selenium WebDriver Mainly Used For?
1. Selenium WebDriver is used to automate webbrowsers
2. It helps testers and developers test web applications automatically instead of doing manual testing.

⭐ Main Applications
1. Automating Web Applications Testin
    -> Used to test websites
    -> Checks if the website works correctly
    -> Support browsers like Chrome , FireFox , Edge , Safari
    -> Only for web applications , not for desktop applications

2. Open Source and Free
    -> Completely free to use
    -> No license cost
    -> Used by companies worldwide

3. Easy to Learn
    -> Simple commands and methods
    -> Beginner friendly
    -> Can quickly start automation test scripts

4. Reduce repetitive work
    -> Automates repetitive test cases
    -> Saves and time effort
    -> Testers can focus on complex testing

5. Cost-Effective for Companies
    -> No Tool purchase cost
    -> Saves time and manspower
    -> Reduces overall testing cost

6. Increased Test Coverage
    -> Automated tests run faster than manual tests
    -> Can test more scenarios
    -> Helps find more bugs

7. Faster testing with parallel execution
    -> Multiple tests can run at the same time
    -> Saves execution time
    -> Useful for large projects

8. Support multiple programming languages
9. Cross platform & browser testing
10. Lighweight tool
    -> No separate server needed
    -> Direct communication with browser
    ->Esay setUp

🌍 Real-World Uses of Selenium
1. Regression Testing
    -> Checks if new changes broke old
    -> Very common use in companies

2. Data Scrapping
    -> Collects data from websites
    -> Used for research and analysis

3. Automating daily Tasks
    -> Sending automated emails
    -> Posting messages automatically
    -> Performing repeated online actions

4. Continuous Integration
    -> Works with tools like Jenkins
    -> Automatically runs tests during builds

5. Cross-Browser Testing
    -> Ensures website works same in all browsers
    